Creating vagrant box for deployment tests.

       Start the box

            vagrant up
            [It should download and install everything, according to the script]

       Package the box

           vagrant package --output maverick32trustpay.box

           vagrant box add 'maverick32trustpay' 'maverick32trustpay.box'

           md5sum maverick32trustpay.box | awk '{print $1}' > maverick32trustpay.box.md5

           scp maverick32trustpay.box* alanz@10.2.2.112:/var/www/incoming/vagrant/boxes/virtualbox-4.1.18/

       Clean up

           vagrant destroy

           This will remove the .vagrant file, and delete the VM from
           virtualbox, freeing up space and avoiding future confusion


           The box is now installed in your local environment. If you
           do not need to make it available to others, get rid of the
           artifacts

           rm maverick32trustpay.box*
